Job Opportunities MVP Prototype  – Database Structure Proposal
University of Wolverhampton Student Engagement Project

Nico Bowen - Database Analyst suggestions 

TEAM NOTES: PLEASE LEAVE SUGGESTIONS AT BOTTOM EDITED

1. Overview
The purpose of this proposal is to outline the core database structure for our Job Opportunities App, designed to support Wolverhampton University students in finding relevant employment.
The app aims to reduce financial stress and increase student engagement by connecting students with suitable work opportunities aligned to their studies and lifestyle.

2. Core Database Tables
Table Name	Key Fields	Purpose / Notes

Jobs	

JobID, Title, Description, Type (FT/PT/Seasonal), FieldOfStudy, Salary, Location, AvgTravelTime, RemoteOption, ApplicationDeadline, CompanyID	Stores all available job listings

Companies	

CompanyID, Name, Industry, Location, ContactDetails, Description, Website	Holds employer and company information

Students

StudentID, UniEmail, Course, YearOfStudy, MaxTravelTime, WorkPreferences, Skills	Contains student profiles and preferences

Applications	

ApplicationID, StudentID, JobID, DateApplied, Status	Records which student has applied for which job

Admins	

AdminID, Name, Email, Role	Used to control and manage administrative access

Feedback (optional)	

FeedbackID, StudentID, JobID, Rating, Comments	Gathers feedback after job applications or experience

3. Relationships Overview

One Company can post many Jobs

A Student can apply to many Jobs, and each Job can receive many Applications (many-to-many relationship)

Admins oversee Students, Companies, and Jobs


4. User Roles & Access Controls

Role	Responsibilities	Access Scope (CRUD)

Student	Create/Edit profile, search & apply for jobs, view application status, give feedback	Read/Write on 

Students, Applications, Feedback

Company	Create/Edit company profile, post/edit jobs, review applicants, update status	Read/Write on Companies, 

Jobs, Applications (own only)

Admin	Manage all data, oversee job postings, moderate users, generate reports	Full Create/Read/Update/Delete on 
all tables

(CRUD = Create, Read, Update, Delete)


5. Example Workflow


[Student]
   │
   ▼
[Browse Jobs] ─▶ [Apply for Job] ─▶ [Applications Table]
   │                          │
   ▼                          ▼
[Save Job / Give Feedback]    [Employer Reviews Application]
   │                                   │
   ▼                                   ▼
    [Reports & Engagement Data for Admins]





6. MVP (Minimum Viable Product) Focus
For the initial prototype:


Implement Jobs, Companies, Students, and Applications tables.

Build role-based access control (Student, Company, Admin) for data security.

Enable search, filtering, and application tracking.

Add simple analytics later for engagement tracking.

Next Step:

Review with the project team to agree on final table fields and relationships before creating the initial database 

schema and connecting it to the prototype app


